---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Victor Em — Engineering Manager, data infrastructure, Stanford.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[900px] px-6 py-16 gxsc-reveal">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-light tracking-tight text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-8 font-display">About</h1>

    <div class="space-y-12 gxsc-reveal gxsc-delay-1">

      <section class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          I'm Victor Em — Engineering Manager for Data Infrastructure at a real-time crypto trading startup in Mountain View, CA.
          I manage a team of seven engineers and stay hands-on with system design, code reviews, and production incident response.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="section-header">Background</h2>
        <p>
          I studied at Stanford (B.S. + M.S., GPA 3.66/3.78) and have spent the last decade at the intersection of data engineering and platform infrastructure.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-3 pt-2">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[160px_1fr] gap-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2025 – Now</span>
            <span>Engineering Manager, Data Infrastructure — Stealth Crypto Startup</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[160px_1fr] gap-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2023 – 2025</span>
            <span>Staff Engineer, ML & Data Platform — SiriusXM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[160px_1fr] gap-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2022 – 2023</span>
            <span>Senior Data Engineer — Meta</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[160px_1fr] gap-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2019 – 2022</span>
            <span>Data Engineering Lead — Disney Streaming Services</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[160px_1fr] gap-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2016 – 2019</span>
            <span>Senior Data Analyst / Data Scientist — Foursquare</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="pt-2">
          My technical depth is in real-time data infrastructure: ClickHouse, NATS streaming, DBT, Postgres CDC pipelines, dimensional modeling.
          I've also done significant work in ML platform infrastructure (Databricks, AWS, IaC) and privacy/compliance data systems at Meta.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="section-header">What I'm Working On Now</h2>
        <p>
          Right now I'm heads-down building real-time data infrastructure for a crypto trading platform —
          ClickHouse + a pub/sub bus + Postgres CDC processing 400+ trades per second, with materialized aggregations
          serving a live web terminal and Telegram trading app. The interesting problems are at the intersection
          of streaming latency, Solana's account model, and keeping a team of seven moving fast without accumulating debt.
        </p>
        <p>
          I also automate as much of my own workflow as possible: session logging, PR review pipelines,
          team status reporting via Claude Code and GitHub Actions. Meta-tooling is something I think about a lot.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="section-header">This Site</h2>
        <p>
          This is a <strong>Technical Workshop</strong> — a living archive of engineering work, system designs, and weekly learnings.
          It's public partly for accountability, partly because I find other engineers' logs useful and want to contribute to that.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 pt-2">
          <li><strong>Logs:</strong> Weekly digests of what I shipped and what I learned.</li>
          <li><strong>Essays:</strong> Long-form posts on systems, management, and technical decisions.</li>
          <li><strong>Resources:</strong> Frameworks and guides I've built up over the years.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="section-header">Outside Work</h2>
        <p>
          I'm President of the Board of Trustees at the <a href="https://www.lfe.foundation/" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">Lambda Phi Epsilon Foundation</a>,
          a 501(c)3 providing need-based and merit-based scholarships to students across 60+ universities.
          We've raised $200K+ in alumni donations since launch. I also built the donation pipeline (PayPal/Stripe → Salesforce → QuickBooks via Zapier).
        </p>
        <p>
          I play Magic: The Gathering at a competitive level (cEDH format) and occasionally build analytics tooling for tournament data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="section-header">Professional Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For my resume, official bio, or professional inquiries:
        </p>
        <a href="https://victorem.me" class="inline-block text-[var(--color-accent)] font-medium hover:underline">victorem.me →</a>
      </section>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-[var(--color-border)] flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 gxsc-reveal gxsc-delay-2">
        <a href="/logs" class="btn btn-primary text-center">
          Read the Logs
        </a>
        <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-secondary text-center">
          Read Essays
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
